 Port Elizabeth - Three suspects were arrested by the Mount Road Cluster Detective Trio Task Team for a house robbery that was allegedly committed on 13 July 2019 in Missionvale, Port Elizabeth. "It is alleged that on the mentioned date, during the night, about seven suspects armed with pangas and knives entered a house in Missionvale and threatened the occupants," said police spokesperson, W/O Alwin Labans. "Various household items were taken from the house. "The Task Team members received information about the possible whereabouts of the suspects and, with assistance of the Anti Gang Unit, the suspects were arrested at various houses in Sedarts grounds, in Missionvale." He said that the suspects will appear in the New Brighton Magistrate's Court on Wednesday on charges of house robbery. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 